URL: https://tglgames.com/stack-rush/

0. game token = "run_token"
1. as always, i find the post request from a test run and use it as a template
2. The game verifies the game token, time, and by "replaying" the "move_log" and compare to result
  2a. When you start a game, you receive a game token, you need to use it for your post request. (The game token also contain a "s" which is a epoch time it use and check as well, but because you use legit game token it doesn't really matter)
  2b. "duration_ms" and "t" in the last "move_log" should be the same and you have to actually wait that time before sending the request after starting the game. e.g. if "duration_ms" is 20000, start the game, wait 20 sec and send the post request
  2c. I just took the first move from my "move_log" copied it a lot of times (you don't need to update the time field) and updated the "blocks_placed", "highest_stack", "perfect_drops", "longest_combo" and "input_pointer"
3. if you send this now, you will still get an error response, but the error will tell you the mistakes, e.g. it will display your score calculated from the "move_log" and the other fields, i just did it over and updated the score with the correct calculated one. (you can ofc also calculate it your self if you want)



